FOR IMMEDIATE CONSIDERATION!!!!<br>
<br>
Top Chef Brooke Williamson and her husband Nick Roberts are currently looking to fill a traveling Sous Chef position.  This is a unique position is for someone that is culinary focused and able to multi-task.   We currently operate 4 restaurants and are in need for sous chef to bounce around and check in/work with the culinary teams in each of the restaurants to ensure consistency and efficiency.  This position works directly under and reports to our CDC.  You must be able to adjust to working in a different kitchen several times a week.<br>
<br>
Qualifications:<br>
-Must have 2+ years of kitchen management experience in a full-service, moderate to high volume restaurant<br>
-Solid track record of success in previous positions, demonstrating upward career tracking<br>
-Strong organizational and communication skills<br>
-Ability to manage a team and multiple tasks<br>
-Ability to facilitate and effectively execute training<br>
-Ability to handle difficult/challenging situations and conversations<br>
-Ability to perform basic math calculations and cost management<br>
-Manager Servesafe Certification<br>
-Read, write, and speak English fluently<br>
-Ability to speak and understand Spanish a plus<br>
-Ability to work 10+ hour shifts with the ability to stand, sit, or walk for extended periods of time<br>
-Ability to grasp, lift and/or carry up to 50lbs as needed<br>
-Understanding of food sanitation and safety standards<br>
-Self Starter/Self Motivator<br>
-Consistent<br>
<br>
Please send resume and salary requirements    </section>

